Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "sestri" in different forms and positions:

1. *Sestri* su danas došle u posetu. (The sisters came to visit today.)
2. Sinoć sam pozvao *sestru* da mi pomogne oko problema. (Last night I called my sister to help me with a problem.)
3. *Sestrić* je jako raspoložen danas. (My nephew is in a really good mood today.)
4. Moja najbolja drugarica mi je kao *sestra*. (My best friend is like a sister to me.)
5. *Sestre* se vole i podržavaju jedna drugu. (The sisters love and support each other.)
6. Njih dve su *sestre bliznakinje*. (Those two are twin sisters.)
7. *Sestričina* torta je uvek najbolja na proslavama. (My niece's cake is always the best at parties.)
8. Ona je *sestra* poznatog glumca. (She is the sister of a famous actor.)
9. Često se svađaju, ali ipak su *sestre*. (They often argue, but they are still sisters.)
10. Proveli su ceo dan zajedno, kao prave *sestre*. (They spent the whole day together, like true sisters.)

I hope these examples help! Let me know if you have any questions.